While Russia is being shunned by the West, it has historic ties with Pretoria as well as close business links through the Brazil, Russia, India, China, and South Africa (Brics) bloc of emerging economies.

Lavrov is due to hold talks with his South African counterpart, Naledi Pandor, in Pretoria.

A protest by anti-Russia demonstrators is planned outside the venue of the talks.

SA plans to hold joint naval exercises, Operation Mosi, with Russia and China next month.

--BBC--